Fixes sphinx build error:
/home/billdev/workspace/tpm2-pytss/docs/SECURITY.md:document isn't included in any toctree

Signed-off-by: Bill Roberts <bill.c.roberts@gmail.com>

cryptography: add module for using TPM keys with the cryptography module

This implements the necessary interfaces to use RSA and ECC keys with the
cryptography modules.
Enabling for example creating a CA or CSR with TPM-backed keys.

Signed-off-by: Erik Larsson <who+github@cnackers.org>

test: skip some FAPI tests if testing agains tpm2-tss master branch.

This is only a temporary fix so a release can be made.

Signed-off-by: Erik Larsson <who+github@cnackers.org>

internal/crypto: fix _MyRSAPrivateNumbers with cryptograpy >= 42.0.1

RSAPrivateNumbers was moved to a rust implementation in 42.0.1.
So inheritance is no longer possible, so turn the class into a
wrapper instead of a subclass.

Fixes #561

Signed-off-by: Erik Larsson <who+github@cnackers.org>

test: disable pcr_set_auth_value and pcr_set_auth_policy tests for swtpm

Since [commit][1] in libtpms setting auth values/policies for PCRs are no longer supported.

[1]: https://github.com/stefanberger/libtpms/commit/af4fc0e66df6d012c61aee7c418148fb261d77a9

Error

The configuration key "build.image" is deprecated. Use "build.os" instead to continue building your project. Read more at https://docs.readthedocs.io/en/stable/config-file/v2.html#build-os
"""

So switch to new format.

CHANGELOG: update for 2.2.0-rc0

Signed-off-by: Erik Larsson <who+github@cnackers.org>

test: skip tests if ECC curves aren't supported.

Some Linux distributions have a limited set of supported ECC curves
in openssl, so instead of finding a curve that fits everyone skip
certain tests on those systems.

Signed-off-by: Erik Larsson <who+github@cnackers.org>

init: provide a better error message for missing symbols

When the there is a difference in versions between build time and
run time libraries for the bindings there might be missing symbols.
So provide a slightly better error message when that happens, as the
usual message is not to clear.

Signed-off-by: Erik Larsson <who+github@cnackers.org>

ci: use tpm2-tools 5.5 by default and tpm2-tss 4.0.1 for coverage job

Signed-off-by: Erik Larsson <who+github@cnackers.org>

README: replace LGTM with CodeQL

lgtm.com is no longer in service, so use CodeQL badges.

Signed-off-by: Erik Larsson <who+github@cnackers.org>

scripts: remove references to TPMS_ALGORITHM_DESCRIPTION

The type TPMS_ALGORITHM_DESCRIPTION and related MU functions has been removed in tpm2-tss 4.0,
so don't link against MU functions so building against older tpm2-tss versions and running
with newer versions work.

Signed-off-by: Erik Larsson <who+github@cnackers.org>

tctildr: use Tss2_TctiLdr_GetInfo to lookup tcti backend

distros may place TCTI backend to different locations than the system
libraries.

This commits makes the tests lookup the backend via
`Tss2_TctiLdr_GetInfo` instead of of LD_LIBRARY_PATH.
